    <!-- Design notes -->
    <mxCell id="70" value="Design Notes:&#xa;• High Cohesion: all operations manage the hold queue lifecycle (place → notify → fulfil/cancel/expire)&#xa;• Controlled Coupling: depends only on HoldRepository, BookRepository, NotificationService&#xa;• Queue ordering uses holdDate ASC (FIFO) — fair queuing ensures QG-3 (Usability / Fairness)&#xa;• processExpiredHolds() designed as a scheduled task (Spring @Scheduled) — supports QG-2 (Reliability)&#xa;• notifyAvailability() decoupled from CirculationService via IHoldService interface" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#999999;fillColor=#f5f5f5;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=1;fontSize=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
      <mxGeometry x="30" y="540" width="720" height="100" as="geometry" />
    </mxCell>

  </root>
